###############################################
# NOTES FOR TESTING


###############################################
# Before running tests:
# 1. Start the server: pnpm dev
# 2. Start ChromaDB: docker run -p 8000:8000 chromadb/chroma
# 3. Get Firebase ID Token from your frontend or Firebase Console
# 4. Replace @firebaseToken with actual token
# 5. Replace @testUserId with your Firebase user ID
# 6. For file uploads, use VS Code REST Client extension or Postman

# Expected Response Times:
# - Health Check: <10ms
# - Search (cached): <50ms
# - Search (uncached): 100-500ms
# - Upload: 5-30 seconds (depending on bookmark count)
# - Get All: <100ms (cached), <500ms (uncached)
# - Add Bookmark: 2-10 seconds (includes crawling)

# Testing Tools:
# - VS Code Extension: REST Client (humao.rest-client)
# - Alternative: Postman, Insomnia, curl, httpie

# How to use with VS Code REST Client:
# 1. Install "REST Client" extension
# 2. Click "Send Request" above any ### separator
# 3. View response in the panel